from what i can see dolfie dreams are resin cast as well. They warn you of the usage of acetone. Which is an good indicator these are resin cast.
You can use acetone to clean up faces. But you need to wash them of with water immediatly after. Since the acetone makes the material go brittle and slimy. So if you have to clean up faces acetone is ok, just dont let it delve. Clean up the face and wash under water instantly after. Long time exposure to acetone will make your doll break. :^(
